FBIS4-59916 "drnes097_c_94008" FBIS-NES-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 Egypt Interior Ministry Releases 38 `Extremists' Interior Ministry Releases 38 `Extremists' NC1805155794 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 18 May 94 NC1805155794 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Detained extremists who have declared their repentance and given up their extremist ideas were released today. Thirty-eight members of various extremist groups were released. This move came after Interior Minister Hasan al-Alfi's decision to implement the Interior Ministry's policy of releasing those detainees who have declare their repentance and recanted their ideas. After leaving the prison of Mazra'at Tura today, those released affirmed to correspondents of international news agencies and newspapers their rejection of extremist ideas. They condemned recent terrorist operations and all extremist ideas. They added that having declared their repentance, they will now campaign for condemnation of extremist ideas. They will warn the youth not to join any group, and tell them to adhere to the teachings of the true religion. A security source also stated that during the coming days, another batch of repentant extremists will be released.
